<title>USA: Nortel touts potential of Latin telecomms.</title>
<headline>Nortel touts potential of Latin telecomms.</headline>
<dateline>MIAMI 1997-05-07</dateline>
<text>
<p>The head of Northern Telecom's Caribbean and Latin American operations said Wednesday he sees the market for telecommunications products and equipment in the region growing to $10 billion by 2000, versus about $6.5 billion now.</p>
<p>&quot;The world truly is looking at Latin America as the next development in globalization,&quot; Gary Donahee, president of Nortel Caribbean and Latin America, told a conference on communications in the region. &quot;Many, many players are going to the markets in various ways.&quot;</p>
<p>Donahee said the countries most critical to Northern Telecom in the area, where it has done business for about 20 years, include Mexico, Colombia, Central America as a regional entity, and Chile.</p>
